enAPI) is present\n9. Documentation is updated (im.md, socket-events.md)\n10. De
sign system components are in packages/design-system\n11. Golden files exist\n12
. Maestro E2E flows exist\n13. Matching service emits `match:created` event and 
ImService listens via `@OnEvent`\n14. Shared types are generated\n\n**Potential 
issues:**\n1. **MessageEntity uses `@PrimaryColumn` for `id` but `sequence_id` i
s auto-increment** - In the migration, `id` is `CHAR(36) NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY` a
nd `sequence_id` is `BIGINT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT`. But in the entity, `id` us
es `@PrimaryColumn("char", { length: 36 })` and `sequence_id` uses `@Column({ ty
pe: "bigint", generated: "increment" })`. This is correct since `id` is the prim
ary key and `sequence_id` is just auto-increment for ordering.\n\nWait, there\'s
a potential issue: In MySQL, you can only have one AUTO_INCREMENT column per tab
le and it must be a key. The migration has `id` as PRIMARY KEY and `sequence_id`
as `BIGINT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT` but `sequence_id` is NOT indexed as a primar
y key or unique key. Actually looking at the migration:\n```sql\nsequence_id BIG
INT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,\n...\nUNIQUE KEY idx_messages_conv_client_msg_id (c
onversation_id, client_message_id)\n```\nMySQL requires AUTO_INCREMENT to be ind
exed. The `sequence_id` has `INDEX idx_messages_sequence_id (sequence_id)` which
satisfies this. So it\'s OK.\n\n2. **MatchingModule does not import ImModule** -
The MatchingService emits `match:created` event via `EventEmitter2`, and `ImServ
ice` listens with `@OnEvent("match:created")`. This is fine because EventEmitter
2 is global.\n\n3. **No push notification service** - This is explicitly out of 
